    <changelog>
      <change date="2011 October 3" revision="6"
      author="Peter O'Gorman" email="pogma@thewrittenword.com">
        <item><para>Update bison dependency from 2.3 to
2.4.3</para></item>
        <item><para>Update diffutils dependency from 2.8.1 to
3.2</para></item>
        <item><para>Add support for AIX 7.1</para></item>
      </change>

      <change date="2011 January 25" revision="5"
      author="Albert Chin-A-Young" email="china@thewrittenword.com">
        <item><para>Apply patch for CVE-2010-2891 (<ulink url="http://www.cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2010-2891">http://www.cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2010-2891</ulink>). 
Buffer overflow in the <command>smiGetNode</command> function in
<command>lib/smi.c</command> allows context-dependent attackers to
execute arbitrary code via an Object Identifier (aka OID) represented
as a numerical string containing many components separated by . (dot)
characters.</para></item>
      </change>

      <change date="2010 October 30" revision="4"
      author="Peter O'Gorman" email="pogma@thewrittenword.com">
        <item><para>Add support for RHEL 6</para></item>
      </change>

      <change date="2010 January 20" revision="3"
      author="Peter O'Gorman" email="pogma@thewrittenword.com">
        <item><para>Reduce optimizations on IRIX to avoid
SEGV</para></item>
      </change>

      <change date="2009 July 1" revision="2"
      author="Albert Chin-A-Young" email="china@thewrittenword.com">
        <item><para>Add support for HP-UX 11.31/PA</para></item>
      </change>
    </changelog>
  </program>
</programs>
